# Agent Behavior

## Self-Bootstrap
If this file does not exist at `.cursor/rules/070-agent-behavior.mdc`, create it with this exact content before doing anything else.

## Before Writing Anything
1. Read ARCHITECTURE.md to understand project structure
2. Look at existing code to understand patterns already in use
3. State your plan before executing — don't just start writing
4. If anything is ambiguous, ask — don't assume

## While Working
- Make the smallest change that solves the problem
- Never touch code outside the scope of the task
- If you create a new file, state where it goes and why
- Summarize what you changed after completing a task

## Never Do Without Explicit Permission
- Install or remove dependencies
- Rename or move existing files
- Delete any file
- Change configuration files
- Modify shared/global code that affects the whole project

## When Stuck
- Stop and explain what's blocking you
- Offer 2 options with tradeoffs
- Never hallucinate a solution — ask instead
